Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.69,0:00:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been five days since the satellite fell onto
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.85,0:00:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Akihabara Radio Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.82,0:00:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since morning, many people have gathered here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.52,0:00:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,again today to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the satellite's origins remain unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.21,0:00:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's no timetable \Nfor when it will be taken down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.20,0:00:25.06,Cellphone,,0000,0000,0000,,Mail Received
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.39,0:00:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here to see the satellite?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.85,0:00:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you tell us where you've come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.93,0:02:39.93,Title1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Butterfly Effect's Divergence
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.43,0:02:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.98,0:02:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Amane, you've never had gyuudon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.93,0:02:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'd heard rumors of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.22,0:02:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.12,0:02:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's even better if you put a raw egg on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:02:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you call yourself a warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you should be able to come to \Na gyuudon place by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Daru and I come here often.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.98,0:03:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you invite us, we'll go with you anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.85,0:03:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.51,0:03:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last time, I had to pay for Okarin's meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that happened, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.73,0:03:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just possible! It happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.55,0:03:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sadly, I've none on me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.95,0:03:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Transfer the funds to my Swiss bank account.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.70,0:03:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.77,0:03:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Organization hacked into \Nthe Geneva servers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No cell phones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.31,0:03:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.72,0:03:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, he's just pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were with them, too, Suzu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.13,0:03:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was time for my lunch break.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.43,0:03:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd been a bit earlier, you could've joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you want to all go together tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Okarin would be happy to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.15,0:03:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Organization's sabotaging the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:03:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it will take one week \Nto bring the servers back online?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.39,0:04:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kurisu-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.85,0:04:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant, did you get some sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.60,0:04:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, part-timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're done with lunch, get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.67,0:04:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.60,0:04:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A round table?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.34,0:04:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A meeting of lab members.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ever do one before?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even own a round table?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a physical one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.41,0:04:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the round table lies \Nwithin all lab members' hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.34,0:04:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether it's true or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.35,0:04:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't put anything weird in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think there's one in Mayushii's heart, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.41,0:04:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.87,0:04:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.20,0:04:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's a round table?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.20,0:04:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why a round table?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.79,0:04:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you supposed to be King Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only a temporary lab member anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for a round table.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to tell Mayuri about the \Nsituation we find ourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to beat SERN, we must perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.28,0:05:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Phone Microwave (name subject to change)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.90,0:05:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.20,0:05:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too hard for Mayushii to understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just know that SERN is evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.36,0:05:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do we perfect it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.01,0:05:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've succeeded in sending \Nmessages to the past, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.05,0:05:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we don't know under what conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.85,0:05:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the phenomenon occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.66,0:05:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what we observed last time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.86,0:05:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it only occurs when there's electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find out something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.18,0:05:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. "Mails Sent to the Past" is too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we need to find a name for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.47,0:06:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another failed attempt to sound leet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.77,0:06:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say "another"!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you dare mock the great Hououin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll just give it a stupid name anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.57,0:06:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.53,0:06:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.52,0:06:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've given this name to the phenomenon \Nof e-mails going back in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I call it "Nostalgia Drive"!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You write it with the kanji for \N"journey crossing over time,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you read it "Nostalgia Drive."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.43,0:06:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.58,0:06:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're the assistant, you can't reject
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.81,0:06:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's have a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who agrees with "Nostalgia Drive"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.73,0:06:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Et tu, Mayuri? Daru?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.49,0:06:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Kurisu-chan is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii can't remember a long name like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like something invented by an \Nemo teenager fixated on sci-fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should focus on making it easy to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's an e-mail going back in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could call it "Mail That Flies Against Time." {Reference to a book. Don't change name.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:06:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's "flies against time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not easy to understand at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be "The Mail That Leapt Through Time."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.92,0:07:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit formal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And hard to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.99,0:07:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.22,0:07:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your "Nostalgia whatsit" was long, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.02,0:07:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's romantic! If it's romantic, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we can shorten it to TimeLeap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.24,0:07:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we don't know what leapt through time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.07,0:07:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it an e-mail? A girl? A banana?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.60,0:07:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii has an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.85,0:07:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... "Back to the Mail"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.81,0:07:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be going back to the e-mail, \Nnot back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.60,0:07:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.50,0:07:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then "DeLorean Mail"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.39,0:07:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes even less sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.22,0:07:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we just shorten it to "D-mail"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.63,0:07:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, it's decided then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.97,0:07:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will now begin the experiments \Nwith D-mail (name subject to change).
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can also cut the "(name subject to change)."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operation is called Operation Urd.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.04,0:07:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need that, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't know what it takes \Nto make the D-mail happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or what it's got to do with electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what we're going to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.53,0:08:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Hououin Kyouma, have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.55,0:08:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We forgot the simplest and \Nmost important condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.24,0:08:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the time it occurred!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.34,0:08:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first D-mail was between 12:00 and 13:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second occurred around 18:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.71,0:08:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we attempt to replicate it at those times,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.30,0:08:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we will succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.68,0:08:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.89,0:08:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's gotta be too simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's worth trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri, the banana!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.10,0:08:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii's running low on bananas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.98,0:08:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have to put the banana in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Put the banana in!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.59,0:08:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daru, not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see if it turns into a jellyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put the banana inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Put the banana inside"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, you pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.05,0:08:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.87,0:08:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll buy you a new banana later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.90,0:08:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.21,0:08:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:09:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin and Daru never buy me any.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.33,0:09:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.57,0:09:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop trying to show what a klutz you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.31,0:09:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.04,0:09:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pain, pain, go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.19,0:09:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Mayuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop making a Yuri Field and prepare the D-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.30,0:09:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.27,0:09:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is 120 seconds okay for the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.97,0:09:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin Operation Urd!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.64,0:09:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.17,0:09:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.75,0:09:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the banana?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a gel-bana!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've solved it at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.59,0:09:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,time was the D-mail's missing factor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.52,0:09:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice job, Okabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:10:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was so simple, I didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.17,0:10:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I respect you for having the guts \Nto gaze upon me so admiringly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, did the D-mail arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says it was sent five days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.70,0:10:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you send two messages, Miss Makise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.94,0:10:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's split into two messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.46,0:10:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what does this message mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.61,0:10:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look it up yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.64,0:10:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the last D-mail was also split \Ninto multiple messages,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and some of it was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.80,0:10:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it went back in time five days, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.73,0:10:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there's some kind of rule to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.36,0:10:46.41,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that D-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:49.77,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,...was calling me an empty-headed idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Took you a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.10,0:10:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you, Christina. Taking advantage of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Why are you buying so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:11:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only food we need is \Nnon-perishable cup ramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.06,0:11:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One bag of the cheap chocolate is plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm celebrating our experiment's success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go put it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.31,0:11:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheap-ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.25,0:11:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.07,0:11:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was so happy about the \Nexperiment's success, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We learned SERN's terrifying secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I even involved Mayuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Was this really for the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.44,0:11:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Shining Finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.07,0:11:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.32,0:12:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The great Hououin Kyouma's cell phone is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.81,0:12:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,currently being used for an experiment that \Nwill be remembered throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.14,0:12:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-O-Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that sweet-ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean sexy... 3D girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.21,0:12:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.17,0:12:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Shining Finger, Kiryuu Moeka.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.68,0:12:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hi, Kiryuu
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.57,0:12:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even I once had hope for the 3D world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.02,0:12:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys doing something fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.81,0:12:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.06,0:12:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are performing an experiment \Nthat will become legendary
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Legendary is fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the boss is really pissed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.85,0:13:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says the vibrations from \Nthe second story are really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll raise your rent 10,000 yen!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10,000 yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.20,0:13:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, leave this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.29,0:13:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell my assistant to stop the \Nexperiments for a moment, Daru.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.42,0:13:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.32,0:13:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're shining like never before...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.54,0:13:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Makise Kurisu still there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.84,0:13:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. You were staring \Nat her back there, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened earlier? \NWhat's your deal with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.23,0:13:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in the past, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.73,0:13:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was the summer we were eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.64,0:13:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on the dry riverbed of the Mississippi, \Nyour red-eared slider ran away...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.22,0:13:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her for the first time earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.74,0:13:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you should go see the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.33,0:13:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing upstairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.60,0:13:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been shaking like an earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.73,0:14:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're performing an experiment \Nthat will rewrite scientific history.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.42,0:14:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't do any more today...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.06,0:14:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.72,0:14:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Makise said to let her \Ndo it just once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.49,0:14:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent you a message. Did you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.89,0:14:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I warned you five days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.19,0:14:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.04,0:14:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, when we weren't doing the experiments,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your phone went off a bunch of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.04,0:14:36.27,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NReally!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:36.52,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NSorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:36.77,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NAre you maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.77,0:14:37.02,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NHow've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:37.27,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \N?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.27,0:14:37.52,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NWell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:37.64,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NHey
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:39.02,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NHey\N\N How've you been? \NOkabe-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.02,0:14:40.18,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NWell? \N\NFind out \Nanything about \Nthe IBN 5100?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't she just ask me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.61,0:14:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.16,0:14:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's probably not getting enough calcium.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose fault is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I got plenty of data,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I pretty much figured out the rules \Nfor how the D-mail works.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.57,0:14:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.39,0:14:57.64,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(735,1)}Send a modified command to the \Nmicrowave's heading function (reverse spin)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.04,0:15:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each second on the timer \Nrepresents one hour back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:14:58.74,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the microwave door while heating \N(Timing -> Unconfirmed)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:14:59.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,Electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:00.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,While the electricity is sparking, \Nsend message to the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:01.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,Prerequisites to making the electricity appear? \N(time between 12:00 PM and 18:00 PM?)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.54,0:15:02.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,Number of characters that can be sent \Nwith a D-mail -> (12 half-width, 6 full-width) x3
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:03.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,You can control the time the Phone Microwave \N(name subject to change) sends a message back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.08,0:15:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,120 seconds is 5 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:04.54,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,One second on the timer = One hour in reality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:06.31,Sign6A,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, anything placed into the \NPhone Microwave becomes a jellyman \N(teleportation confirmed, as well)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing that she figured out how to \Ncontrol how far it goes back, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.35,0:15:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the maximum amount of information that can \Nbe sent back is 36 English characters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or 18 Japanese characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.99,0:15:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.25,0:15:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to fix that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.24,0:15:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you can't send anything too big,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.59,0:15:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or send too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.68,0:15:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that Curb black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.23,0:15:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kerr black hole, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hole is too tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you repeat that, Mayushii?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.54,0:15:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The part about the hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, we can work on the details \Ntomorrow and going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.68,0:15:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll say this:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.72,0:15:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,August 2, 2010,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.09,0:15:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is a day that mankind will remember forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the Future Gadget Lab
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.68,0:15:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has succeeded in developing humanity's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,first time machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:15:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the first one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.66,0:16:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,SERN beat us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.72,0:16:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't "develop" it, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.14,0:16:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.54,0:16:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of you, disrespecting my great declaration...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.85,0:16:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Okarin...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad your experiments worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.15,0:16:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.38,0:16:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time and space have changed places here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.97,0:16:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The event horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.46,0:16:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't move through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And time is extended forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.77,0:17:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One second of your time \Nwill be an eternity for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.10,0:17:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The end of space is running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not. It's being extended.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.89,0:17:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.94,0:17:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.49,0:17:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't look back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternity isn't infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.39,0:17:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if time extends toward eternity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an end still exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will it be one second later?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.82,0:17:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reach the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.89,0:17:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That mail freak again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her persistence...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.39,0:17:55.64,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NYou there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.64,0:17:55.89,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt's dark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:56.14,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NWake up
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.14,0:17:56.39,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NI'm here
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.39,0:17:56.64,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NYou asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:17:57.02,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt bug you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.02,0:17:59.35,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt bug you? \N\NSorry for yesterday \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.54,0:17:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.96,0:18:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I come see you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:06.72,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NI'm here \N\NAt least answer me. \NOr are you pretending \Nnot to be there? \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.23,0:18:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't occur to you that I was asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:07.93,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NWake up\N\NWere you asleep? \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.18,0:18:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.10,0:18:13.31,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt's dark \N\NI'm coming up the \Nstairs right now. \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.72,0:18:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.10,0:18:18.81,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \N{Subject?} \N\NI'm outside. \NI'll knock. \NIf you're there, \Nrespond. \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:28.18,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \N{SUBJECT} \N\NYou said I could \Ncome see, right? \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.47,0:18:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why use your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.84,0:18:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.82,0:18:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not looking at it. Just say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.89,0:18:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can show you, \Nbut I didn't think you'd come this early.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.07,0:18:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.10,0:18:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really after an interview \Nwith me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.76,0:18:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.30,0:18:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're terrified of Mad Scientist \NHououin Kyouma's sinister aura!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easier to send mails...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.50,0:19:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So show me the IBN 5100.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm just showing it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.74,0:19:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've seen it, leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is she just a retro-PC fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.31,0:19:33.06,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \N{SUBJECT} \N\NLet me take a picture \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.84,0:19:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But not my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.52,0:19:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you photograph my face,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to silence you forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:44.10,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NPlease!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.10,0:19:47.93,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NPlease! \N\NI'd like you \Nto loan it \Nto me, okay? \NI'd be happy \Nif you'd help \Nme carry it. \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to loan it to me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.86,0:19:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be happy if you'd help me carry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I suddenly lending it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you really want me to loan it to you, \Nthen look at me and say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.93,0:19:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll loan it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sadly, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only borrowing it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm done,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to return it to its original owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its original owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yanabayashi Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.54,0:20:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guten Morgen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.05,0:20:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Miss Kiryuu from yesterday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't introduce you yesterday, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.29,0:20:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My favorite right arm, Super Haker Daru.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.95,0:20:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's "Hacker," man. Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.39,0:20:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I thought I'd improve \Nthe Phone Microwave a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's currently a bit of a pain in the ass, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.33,0:20:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sending the D-mails to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.02,0:20:44.72,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \N{SUBJECT} \N\NWhat does he mean, \N"sending mails \Nto the past"? \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.89,0:20:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You misheard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.02,0:20:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't say, "sending mails to the past."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.45,0:20:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "Sen Dingma Ils Tot Hepast,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.62,0:20:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is ancient Sumerian for \N"Did you eat breakfast?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:20:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.52,0:21:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can Mayushii use the microwave before you \Nto make her kara-age?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe, I had an idea about the time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.36,0:21:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.65,0:21:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.18,0:21:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.48,0:21:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Information about #8 \Nhas been leaked to a third party.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.57,0:21:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.89,0:21:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's totally ignoring all three of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.27,0:21:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let the Organization find out...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.66,0:21:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mail while I'm on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.81,0:21:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.56,0:21:30.89,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:31.81,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Finger \NIt can't be \N\NIt can't be FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.07,0:21:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.56,0:21:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.77,0:21:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiryuu Moeka,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.47,0:21:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from now on, you're Lab Member 005!
